Blueline Protection – Privacy Policy
Last Updated: 12/11/2025

1. Data We Collect  
The Bot may collect and store the following information:  
• Discord server IDs  
• Channel and role IDs selected during setup  
• Moderation logs (warnings, kicks, bans, timeouts, etc.)  
• User-provided verification data  
• Basic metadata required for licensing validation  

2. How Data Is Used  
Data is used solely to provide Bot features, including:  
• Moderation logging  
• Verification processing  
• Anti-spam and raid protection  
• License validation  
• Configuration storage  

3. How Data Is Stored  
All data is stored securely on private infrastructure accessible only to the Bot owner.

4. Data Sharing  
We do not sell, rent, or share any user data.  
Data is not shared with third parties unless required by law.

5. User Rights  
Users may request:  
• Removal of stored moderation logs  
• Removal of verification data  
• Clarification of what data is stored on their server  
Requests can be submitted to: Discord @korzak

6. Data Retention  
Data may be kept as long as the Bot remains in the server or as long as required for licensing enforcement.

7. Children  
The Bot does not target users under 13 and follows Discord’s minimum age requirements.

8. Changes to This Policy  
We may update this Policy at any time. Continued use of the Bot indicates acceptance of updates.
